# Cloudflare Authenticated Origin Pulls (AOP) CA pinned fingerprint.
#
# Source of truth for the AOP CA bytes that edge-ingress trusts at
# /etc/edge-ingress/cloudflare/origin-pull-ca.pem. Captured once via
# `refresh-cloudflare-ips.sh --bootstrap` and committed; thereafter
# every weekly CI run verifies the live Cloudflare-published bytes
# still hash to this value. A mismatch means Cloudflare rotated the
# CA and an operator must follow the rotation runbook in
# docs/architecture/edge-cloudflare-envoy.md.
#
# Format: single line, lowercase hex SHA-256, no colons.
#
# ============================================================================
# TODO: BOOTSTRAP REQUIRED. This file currently contains no fingerprint.
# ============================================================================
#
# Until populated:
#   - the weekly CI refresh job (`make cf-refresh-ips`) exits 1 with a
#     clear bootstrap-required message,
#   - the AOP CA preflight init-container on edge-ingress
#     (helm/edge-ingress/templates/deployment.yaml) refuses to start
#     edge-ingress pods if the Vault-resolved CA is empty.
#
# To populate (run once on a workstation with Cloudflare network access
# and credentials to push a Vault payload):
#
#   make cf-bootstrap-aop-ca
#
# That command runs `refresh-cloudflare-ips.sh --bootstrap`, which:
#   1. Fetches the live Cloudflare AOP CA from
#      https://developers.cloudflare.com/ssl/static/authenticated_origin_pull_ca.pem
#   2. Writes its SHA-256 fingerprint into THIS file (overwriting this
#      placeholder).
#   3. Writes the PEM bytes to ./origin-pull-ca.pem in this directory.
#
# Then commit both files in the same change:
#
#   git add deployments/cloudflare/origin-pull/aop-ca.sha256
#   git add -f deployments/cloudflare/origin-pull/origin-pull-ca.pem
#   git commit -m "chore(cloudflare): bootstrap AOP CA pin"
#
# Separately, push the same PEM bytes to Vault at the path read by
# the cloudflare-aop-ca ExternalSecret:
#   etradie/services/edge-ingress/<env>/cloudflare/aop_ca
# with key `aop_ca` set to the literal PEM content. After that, the
# preflight init-container on edge-ingress will validate the bytes
# at pod start and the platform can roll out.
